    • Method Detail

      • preProcess

        ResourceFinder.ResourceFinderCallbackResult preProcess​(java.lang.String resourceName,
                                                       long filesize,
                                                       long timestamp,
                                                       java.io.InputStream inputStream)
                                                throws java.io.IOException
        This method is only invoked for archive resources, before that archive has been read or recursed into. Both archives and standard files will be passed to the #postProcess(String, long, long, InputStream) method.
        Parameters:
        resourceName - full resource name
        filesize - the size of the (uncompressed) resource, or -1 if this is unknown (some archives do not store this information)
        timestamp - the timestamp of the resource
        inputStream - an inputStream which can be used to retrieve the contents of the resource
        Returns:
        a ResourceFinderCallbackResult which can be used to abort the search or modify/wrap the inputStream being searched.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • postProcess

        ResourceFinder.ResourceFinderCallbackResult postProcess​(java.lang.String resourceName,
                                                        long filesize,
                                                        long timestamp,
                                                        java.io.InputStream inputStream,
                                                        ResourceFinder.ResourceFinderCallbackResult preProcessResult)
                                                 throws java.io.IOException
        This method is invoked for each resource that matches the search criteria specified in the containing ResourceFinder class. This method is not responsible for closing the supplied inputStream.
        Parameters:
        resourceName - full resource name
        filesize - the size of the (uncompressed) resource, or -1 if this is unknown (some archives do not store this information)
        timestamp - the timestamp of the resource
        inputStream - an inputStream which can be used to retrieve the contents of the resource
        Returns:
        a ResourceFinderCallbackResult which can be used to abort the search
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an operation on the inputStream fails
